Class EvaluationCache

java.lang.Object
engine.forPlayer.forAI.EvaluationCache
public class EvaluationCache extends Object
The EvaluationCache class provides a thread-safe cache for chess board evaluations to avoid redundant calculations during search operations. It uses Zobrist hashing combined with search depth as the cache key for efficient and accurate lookups. The cache automatically manages its size by evicting entries when it reaches capacity limits.

This class follows the singleton pattern to ensure consistent caching across the entire chess engine. Cache statistics are maintained to monitor hit rates and performance characteristics.

Author:
Aaron Ho

  • Method Details

    • get

      public static EvaluationCache get()
      Returns the singleton instance of the EvaluationCache.
      Returns:
      The singleton EvaluationCache instance.

    • store

      public void store(Board board, int depth, double score)
      Stores an evaluation score in the cache for the specified board position and search depth. If the cache is at capacity, entries are automatically evicted before storing the new value.
      Parameters:
      board - The chess board position being evaluated.
      depth - The search depth used for the evaluation.
      score - The evaluation score to cache.

    • probe

      public Double probe(Board board, int depth)
      Retrieves a cached evaluation score for the specified board position and search depth. Updates cache statistics based on whether the lookup was successful.
      Parameters:
      board - The chess board position to look up.
      depth - The search depth used for the evaluation.
      Returns:
      The cached evaluation score, or null if not found in cache.

    • getStats

      public String getStats()
      Returns a formatted string containing cache performance statistics including entry count, hit rate percentage, and total hits and misses.
      Returns:
      A string representation of cache statistics.

    • clear

      public void clear()
      Clears all entries from the cache and resets hit and miss statistics to zero.

    • clearSomeEntries

      private void clearSomeEntries()
      Removes approximately half of the cache entries to prevent excessive memory usage. This method is called automatically when the cache reaches its maximum size.
